Let $S$ be the set of integers from 1 to 100 that are not divisible by 3.  Then $S$ has 67 elements.  We can take out every third element of $S$ to get a set of integers, none of which is 3 times another.  This set has $\frac{2}{3} \cdot 67 = \boxed{44\text{ elements}}.$

